## Why This Is Asked
Demonstrates practical, production-ready handling of partial data quality failures in a Delta Live Tables pipeline, balancing correctness with availability.

## Key Concepts
- Staging vs downstream separation
- Expectations-based quality checks
- Quarantine and audit of invalid data
- Late data handling with watermarking
- Deduplication strategies across micro-batches

## Code Example
```javascript
import dlt
import pyspark.sql.functions as F

@dlt.table
def raw_events():
  return spark.read.format("cloudFiles").option("cloudFiles.format","json").load("/mnt/events/raw")

@dlt.table
def valid_events():
  df = dlt.read("raw_events")
  return df.filter(F.col("event_time").isNotNull() & F.col("user_id").isNotNull())

@dlt.table
def invalid_events():
  raw = dlt.read("raw_events")
  valid_ids = dlt.read("valid_events").select("event_id").distinct()
  return raw.join(valid_ids, "event_id", "left_anti")

@dlt.table
def clean_events():
  return dlt.read("valid_events")
```

